## Refactors applied (FIND-205, FIND-208, FIND-211)

### FIND-211: appShellStore start/stop reset callbacks removed
File: promptnotes/src/lib/ui/app-shell/appShellStore.ts
- writable("Loading", startFn) → writable("Loading") (no start/stop callbacks)
- Removed unconditional set("Loading") on first subscribe and on last unsubscribe
- These callbacks violated REQ-020 (Loading→Loading transitions suppressed by bootAttempted),
  REQ-021 (writes from store module itself bypass authority boundary), and caused PROP-010
  third test to fail (subscribe after boot reset store back to Loading)
- Added __resetForTesting__() export for test isolation (replaces the production-time side-effect hack)
- Added __resetBootFlagForTesting__() to bootOrchestrator.ts for boot flag reset

### FIND-208: Double withIpcTimeout wrap eliminated
File: promptnotes/src/lib/ui/app-shell/tauriAdapter.ts
- createTauriAdapter.invokeAppStartup no longer wraps with withIpcTimeout
  (bootOrchestrator owns the single wrap point for invokeAppStartup)
- tryVaultPath and invokeConfigureVault still wrap per REQ-022
  (they are called from vaultModalLogic without any other timeout guard)
- withIpcTimeout now uses clearTimeout in .finally() to prevent leaked sentinel timers

### FIND-205: PROP-011 audit tightened
File: promptnotes/src/lib/ui/app-shell/__tests__/effectful-isolation.test.ts
- Audit pattern now scans for BOTH appShellStore.set( / .update( AND setAppShellState( calls
- ALLOWED_WRITERS set expanded to include appShellStore.ts, bootOrchestrator.ts, vaultModalLogic.ts
  (the authority module + the two indirection callers are explicitly allowed; any NEW caller fails)
- This closes the bypass hole where modules used setAppShellState() to evade the literal pattern

